{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ba1cf2f6-2fe5-40ce-b65b-1b4648ef13bd","content":"Two things change with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n### 1. Filter syntax changes\nMTP uses `--filter` but with **different operators**:\n\n| VSTest (v2) | MTP (v3) |\n|---|---|\n| `~` (contains) | `~=` |\n| `&` (and) | `&` (same) |\n| `Category` | `Trait` (with key) |\n\nYour old filter:\n```\n--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nBecomes:\n```\n--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~=IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nThe `~` → `~=` is the critical change. The `Category=Smoke` trait filter stays the same because xUnit v3's MTP adapter maps `[Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]` to the `Category` property automatically.\n\n### 2. Runner invocation\nWith `UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner` + `OutputType=Exe`, you can also run the test executable directly:\n\n```bash\n# Via dotnet test (still works, translates filter internally):\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~=IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n\n# Or invoke the executable directly:\n./TestProject --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~=IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nYour `.csproj` and test code look correct for v3 — no source changes needed.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4210c960-384d-4c5b-a49b-a834dda8ffa9","outputTokens":365,"requestId":"7C41:5115A:141B070:16AD34D:69F94322"},"id":"c60402cf-a777-4dc5-b4d7-12ac80303a5d","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:09:01.028Z","parentId":"05d68664-9726-41b5-8a09-ab525d857d2b"}
